          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / Culver City, CA</p>
  <h1>Senior Network Engineer at Riot Games</h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p>As one of the most popular PC games today, League of Legends is reshaping PC gaming and core gamers perception of virtual goods. Riot Games (named a Top 30 developer by Game Developer Magazine), the publisher and developer of League of Legends, is experiencing a period of rapid growth, doubling the size of the company in the past year. With over 4 MM players in their debut title across the US and Europe, and numerous awards (including IGN.com’s Readers' Choice for Best Multiplayer Game for League of Legends), Riot Games has also pioneered an innovative live development model and is looking to expand its production capabilities.</p>

<p>The Senior Network Engineer position is responsible for managing and overseeing all aspects of network engineering related to the company’s business and online games.   The role involves working with Riot’stechnology groups, development teams, and partners to develop, implement, maintain, and monitor network infrastructure and ensure the highest levels of reliability and stability. This role will be responsible for our global network infrastructure supporting one of the most played games on the Internet.</p>

<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>

<p>•Design, implement, and support the company’s global networkinfrastructure including Local Area Network, Wide Area Network, Internet, remote access systems, and authentication platforms.</p>

<p>•Assist in the development of information security policies, standards, procedures, and checklists</p>

<p>•Responsible for network capacity planning, performance tuning, and troubleshooting.</p>

<p>•Manage and maintain network monitoring systems</p>

<p>•Install, configure, and maintain network and host based intrusion prevention systems, firewalls, and other security devices</p>

<p>•Respond to and analyze security system alerts and incident reports</p>

<p>•Proactively assess potential items of risk and vulnerability in the network&amp; systems</p>

<p>•Manage multiple projects simultaneously and complete them on schedule</p>

<p>•Ensure procedures and processes are clearly and accurately documented and implemented</p>

<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>

<p>•Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science or other related field or equivalent knowledge with 8 years of related professional experience.</p>

<p>•Subject Matter Expert in IP routing protocols including BGP, EIGRP, OSPF, IP Multicast, MPLS.</p>

<p>•Proficiency working with VLAN, VRF, HSRP, Port Security, Traffic Shaping, Priority Queuing, Class of Service (CoS)</p>

<p>•Experience with both wireless networking in a corporate environment and Ethernet switching in both corporate and production environments.</p>

<p>•Must possess an understanding of TCP/IP, access control lists (ACLs), security, firewalls and network traffic analysis. In addition, must be Internet savvy in a production environment with regards to security, DNS, SMTP, SNMP, syslog, and Virtual Private Networks (VPN).</p>

<p>•In depth knowledge and experience with concepts and issues related to computing and infrastructure security.</p>

<p>•Experience with vulnerability assessment tools, packet analyzers,&amp; security management suites</p>

<p>•Excellent oral and written communication skills with a proven ability to effectively interact with all levels of employees.</p>

<p>•Ability to multi-task and work well under pressure in a fast-paced on-time deliverable environment</p>

<p>•Must be self-motivated and able to work effectively both alone and as part of a team</p>

<p>•Some travel may be required</p>

<p><strong>Preferred:</strong></p>

<p>•In depth experience with multiple vendor’s hardware, including Cisco and Juniper.</p>

<p>•Network hardware vendor certification (CCNP, CCIE, JNCIS, JNCIE, etc)</p>

<p>•Experience with VoIP and SIP</p>

<p>•Experience working with Linux and Windows operating systems in production environments</p>

<p>If you are a top-notch Senior Network Engineer who wants the opportunity to innovate with a creative and talented team and have a positive, “can do” attitude, we want to hear from you!</p>

<p>Riot games is paying salaries that are competitive with the enterprise software industry.</p>

<p>NO RECRUITERS. NO PHONE CALLS. WE DO NOT ACCEPT WALK-INS OR PHONE CALLS TO OUR OFFICE, FAILURE TO FOLLOW THIS DIRECTIVE WILL RESULT IN IMMEDIATE DISQUALIFICATION FROM ANY POSITION AT RIOT GAMES.</p>
</div><!-- /.column.main -->

